{"ts":"2026-07-14T16:46:59.756Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-albl"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-557: contract layer intercepts -h/--help before variadic-positional handlers, blocking legitimate positional content"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Host contract/help layer treats a standalone -h/--help token as a global help request BEFORE the command handler runs, even for commands declaring a variadic positional whose content legitimately contains such tokens (Cypher, shell snippets, search expressions). Repro: an extension command 'pm pm-graph query <cypher-query...>' given 'pm pm-graph query WITH 1 AS h RETURN -h' prints contract-layer usage and never invokes the handler; extension-side help checks on context.args are dead code because the host short-circuits first. Quoted single-arg usage works. Impact: agents composing command lines programmatically get a help screen instead of execution, and extension authors have NO opt-out. Fix direction (from GH-557): respect and strip a '--' end-of-flags separator so everything after it reaches context.args verbatim, and/or a passthrough/raw attribute on variadic positional declarations in the command contract; expose raw argv as fallback. Class framing: this is contract-declared argument semantics (same family as pm-fgih convergence and pm-evav real-CLI-boundary flag erasure) — fix at the contract layer once, not per command. Found hardening unbraind/pm-graph query/neighbors."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":[]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-14T16:46:59.756Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-14T16:46:59.756Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":240},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"A variadic positional can be declared passthrough (or '--' separator is respected and stripped) so -h/--help/--json tokens after it reach the handler verbatim at the real CLI boundary; global help still renders for the command when no passthrough content is present; behavior covered by real-boundary regression tests including an extension variadic command; contract docs + generated CLI contracts document the opt-out"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-ugqx"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":75},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-evav","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-14T16:46:59.756Z"},{"id":"pm-fgih","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-14T16:46:59.756Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"dff70dc00c0fc7a741114eaf1d86b20e5bd56d467c5363112a371cf2350ebde7","message":""}
